Smoked Ketchup Recipe:
Combine 1 cup of tomato puree, 1/4 cup of white vinegar, 1/4 cup of brown sugar, 1/2 teaspoon of salt, and 1/8 teaspoon of ground cloves in a saucepan.
Add 1/2 teaspoon of smoked paprika and sauté for 2 minutes.
Bring the mixture to a boil, then reduce the heat and simmer for 20 minutes. Maple Ketchup Recipe:
Combine 1 cup of tomato puree, 1/4 cup of apple cider vinegar, 1/4 cup of maple syrup, 1/2 teaspoon of salt, and 1/8 teaspoon of ground cloves in a saucepan.
Bring the mixture to a boil, then reduce the heat and simmer for 20 minutes. 